     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "ChebyshevPoints[n] returns a list of n Chebyshev points of the first \
kind required to uniquely determine the Chebyshev expansion coefficients of a \
polynomial of degree n - 1. ChebyshevPoints[n -> parity] returns a list of n \
Chebyshev points of the first kind required to uniquely determine the \
Chebyshev coefficients of a polynomial of parity (\\[PlusMinus]1 for even and \
odd parity, respectively). ChebyshevPoints[spec, kind] returns the Chebyshev \
points of kind (kind = 1 for the first kind or kind = 2 for the second kind). \
ChebyshevPoints[spec, kind, {a, b}] or ChebyshevPoints[spec, kind, \
Interval[{a, b}]] returns the Chebyshev points over Interval[{a, b}].", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "ChebyshevPoints", 
